      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TORONADO ROCKET (1) only warmed late when resuming, then took a nice step forward second-up when racing on the speed and fighting on gamely into second behind a handy winner. Peaking now and gets the services of gun apprentice Holly Nottle. Can land a winning blow. BRAVE DRAGON (3) was a barnstorming winner fresh at Albany to get off the mark. Couldn't quite repeat the dose second-up but that was a bit tougher company. Peaking now third-up and will be doing his best work late again. REBELS (6) returns and makes his stable debut for the Webster barn. His best Victorian figures measure up well for this and C Parnham's booking is a good push. DOMINANT FORCE (8) resumes and will be fitter for a recent trial, looks a top three chance. BARNEY ROMMEL (2) can cause a late scare if they overdo it in front.",
